        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 2:15PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 215 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Talona, or 7 miles
south of Ellijay, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Ellijay, East Ellijay, Talona, Cartecay, Roy, Roundtop, and Blaine.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
